🏗 2️⃣ Architecture (How It Works Internally)
🔹 1. Wake Word Layer

Continuously listens using microphone

Uses Porcupine (pvporcupine) engine

Detects custom wake word file (.ppn)

If detected →
→ Triggers UI to open
→ Speaks “Yes, I’m listening”

🔹 2. Backend Layer (FastAPI)

Built using:

FastAPI

Uvicorn

Handles:

/command

/api/weather

/api/news

/api/stocks

/toggle-tts

Routes command to:

Apps handler

Web handler

File handler

System handler

AI Brain (fallback)

🔹 3. AI Processing Layer

Uses:

Custom Brain.py

Local logic / LLM integration

Rule-based command routing

If system command found → execute
Else → AI generates response

🔹 4. UI Layer

Built using:

HTML

CSS

JavaScript

Three.js (3D globe animation)

Features:

Animated AI globe

Live Weather

Live News

Stock Updates

Command buttons

Chat system

Mic input

TTS toggle

Window controls

🔹 5. Desktop Layer

Uses:

pywebview → creates desktop window

pystray → system tray

Pillow → tray icon

threading → background wake listener

🔹 6. Packaging

Uses:

PyInstaller

Bundled wake word files

Standalone .exe

Windows startup integration

